        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 24 at 6:01PM CST by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 601 PM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edna, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Edna, Ganado, Lolita, Lake Texana Dam, and Vanderbilt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

This storm may intensify, so be certain to monitor local radio
stations and available television stations for additional information
and possible warnings from the National Weather Service.</instruction>
